Data Structures and Algorithms:

Overview
Focuses on the fundamentals of Data Structures and Algorithms (DSA).
Covers commonly used data structures such as arrays and linked lists.
Introduces searching algorithms like Linear Search and Binary Search.
Explains sorting algorithms such as Bubble Sort, Quick Sort, and Merge Sort.
Includes hands-on coding exercises to apply DSA concepts to real-world problems.
Emphasizes writing efficient, scalable, and optimized code.
